{"acceptance_decision": "accepted", "access_date": "2026-06-22", "australian_relation": "Northern Territory public-domain ethnographic text.", "candidate_status": "accepted", "canonical_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/aus/ntna/ntna13.htm", "coordinate_evidence_note": "", "cultural_sensitivity": "moderate", "duplicate_check_status": "source_url_external_id_and_excerpt_hash_checked", "ethics_review_status": "public_context_reviewed", "evidence_summary": "The penalties for eating these are as follows:--Jimeribunna, the child is born with yaws; Brutpenniweir, the child is born with a sore nose and mouth; Karakera, the child has sores under its arms; Kalerungeni, the child has sore feet and tongue, and, if a boy, its penis is abnormal; Kulawura, a spirit is supposed to take the child away and bury it in the mound nest of a jungle,", "external_id": "sprint-ista-northern-austral:ntna13:spirit:001", "geocode_source": "", "geocode_verification_status": "", "humanoid_basis": "explicit_supernatural_or_anomalous_person_form_agent", "latitude": "", "location_precision": "region", "location_role": "cultural_association_region", "location_text": "Northern Territory, NT", "longitude": "", "narrative_type": "spirit_person_narrative", "publication_date_text": "1914", "publication_or_organisation": "Native Tribes of the Northern Territory of Australia; Baldwin Spencer", "publicness_status": "public_domain_public_web", "quality_class": "B", "raw_metadata_json": {"chapter": "Magic and Medicine", "evidence_sha256": "8a4984adfe2ce1d5a72e475da13ab273c1cc932008a7a1d903538d995a8975e8", "route_id": "sprint_ista_northern_australia_exact_texts", "scope_classifier": "term_and_person_form_gate_v1", "section_id": "ntna13", "source_family": "structured_public_domain_books"}, "rejection_reason": "", "rights_access_status": "public_access_text_available", "secondary_role": "source_grounded_section_record", "source_label": "spirit", "source_name": "Internet Sacred Text Archive", "source_tier": "A", "source_type": "public_domain_transcribed_book", "title": "spirit in Magic and Medicine", "url": "https://sacred-texts.com/aus/ntna/ntna13.htm"}
{"acceptance_decision": "accepted", "access_date": "2026-06-22", "australian_relation": "Northern Territory public-domain ethnographic text.", "candidate_status": "accepted", "canonical_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/aus/ntna/ntna13.htm", "coordinate_evidence_note": "", "cultural_sensitivity": "moderate", "duplicate_check_status": "source_url_external_id_and_excerpt_hash_checked", "ethics_review_status": "public_context_reviewed", "evidence_summary": "(3) After the child is born, and while it is young, the woman must not drink out of a deep water hole, the water must not reach above her knees; the husband tells the woman that she must not break this rule or the child will die. Also, she must not eat fish out of a deep water hole. They believe that if the child were to see its Mother drinking out of a deep water hole its spirit would Immediately leave its body, run to the water hole, and be drawn under and swallowed up by a Numereji snake. If,", "external_id": "sprint-ista-northern-austral:ntna13:spirit:002", "geocode_source": "", "geocode_verification_status": "", "humanoid_basis": "explicit_supernatural_or_anomalous_person_form_agent", "latitude": "", "location_precision": "region", "location_role": "cultural_association_region", "location_text": "Northern Territory, NT", "longitude": "", "narrative_type": "spirit_person_narrative", "publication_date_text": "1914", "publication_or_organisation": "Native Tribes of the Northern Territory of Australia; Baldwin Spencer", "publicness_status": "public_domain_public_web", "quality_class": "B", "raw_metadata_json": {"chapter": "Magic and Medicine", "evidence_sha256": "e016acb48adc99440e2b095d82f8948d64965e9ed2bd76a6477da1bcc4fb4a94", "route_id": "sprint_ista_northern_australia_exact_texts", "scope_classifier": "term_and_person_form_gate_v1", "section_id": "ntna13", "source_family": "structured_public_domain_books"}, "rejection_reason": "", "rights_access_status": "public_access_text_available", "secondary_role": "source_grounded_section_record", "source_label": "spirit", "source_name": "Internet Sacred Text Archive", "source_tier": "A", "source_type": "public_domain_transcribed_book", "title": "spirit in Magic and Medicine", "url": "https://sacred-texts.com/aus/ntna/ntna13.htm"}
{"acceptance_decision": "accepted", "access_date": "2026-06-22", "australian_relation": "Northern Territory public-domain ethnographic text.", "candidate_status": "accepted", "canonical_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/aus/ntna/ntna13.htm", "coordinate_evidence_note": "", "cultural_sensitivity": "moderate", "duplicate_check_status": "source_url_external_id_and_excerpt_hash_checked", "ethics_review_status": "public_context_reviewed", "evidence_summary": "by any chance, the mother breaks the rule, the father, mother, and child, accompanied by a medicine man, go to the water hole. The father gives the mother a little water in a bark basket. The spirit of the child is attracted, comes up, and is caught by the medicine man, who alone can see it. He immediately places it in the mother's head, from which it passes down into her breast and the child, who is at once put to the breast, drinks it in with its mother's milk, or Kumilungornu. If the father finds out, when the woman is away, that she has been drinking at a deep water hole, he will at once go to the latter with a medicine man,.", "external_id": "sprint-ista-northern-austral:ntna13:spirit:003", "geocode_source": "", "geocode_verification_status": "", "humanoid_basis": "explicit_supernatural_or_anomalous_person_form_agent", "latitude": "", "location_precision": "region", "location_role": "cultural_association_region", "location_text": "Northern Territory, NT", "longitude": "", "narrative_type": "descriptive_belief_record", "publication_date_text": "1914", "publication_or_organisation": "Native Tribes of the Northern Territory of Australia; Baldwin Spencer", "publicness_status": "public_domain_public_web", "quality_class": "B", "raw_metadata_json": {"chapter": "Magic and Medicine", "evidence_sha256": "2bc31d60d9b67919dac619fadd9c8ebfbda30084374f98ae6293832e565fcc0d", "route_id": "sprint_ista_northern_australia_exact_texts", "scope_classifier": "term_and_person_form_gate_v1", "section_id": "ntna13", "source_family": "structured_public_domain_books"}, "rejection_reason": "", "rights_access_status": "public_access_text_available", "secondary_role": "source_grounded_section_record", "source_label": "spirit", "source_name": "Internet Sacred Text Archive", "source_tier": "A", "source_type": "public_domain_transcribed_book", "title": "spirit in Magic and Medicine", "url": "https://sacred-texts.com/aus/ntna/ntna13.htm"}
{"acceptance_decision": "accepted", "access_date": "2026-06-22", "australian_relation": "Northern Territory public-domain ethnographic text.", "candidate_status": "accepted", "canonical_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/aus/ntna/ntna13.htm", "coordinate_evidence_note": "", "cultural_sensitivity": "moderate", "duplicate_check_status": "source_url_external_id_and_excerpt_hash_checked", "ethics_review_status": "public_context_reviewed", "evidence_summary": "He was feeling very bad indeed and an old medicine man said to him ameina jau, ngeinyimma kutjeri, what have you eaten (to make) you ill?", "external_id": "sprint-ista-northern-austral:ntna13:medicine-man:004", "geocode_source": "", "geocode_verification_status": "", "humanoid_basis": "explicit_supernatural_or_anomalous_person_form_agent", "latitude": "", "location_precision": "region", "location_role": "cultural_association_region", "location_text": "Northern Territory, NT", "longitude": "", "narrative_type": "descriptive_belief_record", "publication_date_text": "1914", "publication_or_organisation": "Native Tribes of the Northern Territory of Australia; Baldwin Spencer", "publicness_status": "public_domain_public_web", "quality_class": "B", "raw_metadata_json": {"chapter": "Magic and Medicine", "evidence_sha256": "879e9d65ead8ec0b17c2cb41f3ed76b31bc39a451a2b305d288527670a83f357", "route_id": "sprint_ista_northern_australia_exact_texts", "scope_classifier": "term_and_person_form_gate_v1", "section_id": "ntna13", "source_family": "structured_public_domain_books"}, "rejection_reason": "", "rights_access_status": "public_access_text_available", "secondary_role": "source_grounded_section_record", "source_label": "Medicine man", "source_name": "Internet Sacred Text Archive", "source_tier": "A", "source_type": "public_domain_transcribed_book", "title": "Medicine man in Magic and Medicine", "url": "https://sacred-texts.com/aus/ntna/ntna13.htm"}
{"acceptance_decision": "accepted", "access_date": "2026-06-22", "australian_relation": "Northern Territory public-domain ethnographic text.", "candidate_status": "accepted", "canonical_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/aus/ntna/ntna13.htm", "coordinate_evidence_note": "", "cultural_sensitivity": "moderate", "duplicate_check_status": "source_url_external_id_and_excerpt_hash_checked", "ethics_review_status": "public_context_reviewed", "evidence_summary": "The spirit, or Iwaiyu, of Kuljoanjo had twisted itself round inside his body and, every now and then, came out through his forehead, rattled its teeth and hissed and looked straight into his eyes.", "external_id": "sprint-ista-northern-austral:ntna13:spirit:005", "geocode_source": "", "geocode_verification_status": "", "humanoid_basis": "explicit_supernatural_or_anomalous_person_form_agent", "latitude": "", "location_precision": "region", "location_role": "cultural_association_region", "location_text": "Northern Territory, NT", "longitude": "", "narrative_type": "spirit_person_narrative", "publication_date_text": "1914", "publication_or_organisation": "Native Tribes of the Northern Territory of Australia; Baldwin Spencer", "publicness_status": "public_domain_public_web", "quality_class": "B", "raw_metadata_json": {"chapter": "Magic and Medicine", "evidence_sha256": "32a97a0ff7226e3084755b4c246c6c90ede6162e43b93c9ce22dd470c291eb75", "route_id": "sprint_ista_northern_australia_exact_texts", "scope_classifier": "term_and_person_form_gate_v1", "section_id": "ntna13", "source_family": "structured_public_domain_books"}, "rejection_reason": "", "rights_access_status": "public_access_text_available", "secondary_role": "source_grounded_section_record", "source_label": "spirit", "source_name": "Internet Sacred Text Archive", "source_tier": "A", "source_type": "public_domain_transcribed_book", "title": "spirit in Magic and Medicine", "url": "https://sacred-texts.com/aus/ntna/ntna13.htm"}
{"acceptance_decision": "accepted", "access_date": "2026-06-22", "australian_relation": "Northern Territory public-domain ethnographic text.", "candidate_status": "accepted", "canonical_url": "https://sacred-texts.com/aus/ntna/ntna13.htm", "coordinate_evidence_note": "", "cultural_sensitivity": "moderate", "duplicate_check_status": "source_url_external_id_and_excerpt_hash_checked", "ethics_review_status": "public_context_reviewed", "evidence_summary": "The natives, realising the gravity of the case, had sent away to a place, called Oenpelli, fourteen miles away, for a special, celebrated medicine man, named Morpun, who fortunately happened to be reincarnated at that time.", "external_id": "sprint-ista-northern-austral:ntna13:medicine-man:006", "geocode_source": "", "geocode_verification_status": "", "humanoid_basis": "explicit_supernatural_or_anomalous_person_form_agent", "latitude": "", "location_precision": "region", "location_role": "cultural_association_region", "location_text": "Northern Territory, NT", "longitude": "", "narrative_type": "descriptive_belief_record", "publication_date_text": "1914", "publication_or_organisation": "Native Tribes of the Northern Territory of Australia; Baldwin Spencer", "publicness_status": "public_domain_public_web", "quality_class": "B", "raw_metadata_json": {"chapter": "Magic and Medicine", "evidence_sha256": "bda6f7aa863c425227d8c10c81702ae5c0f25c19e061f7d85f8411a1f32c82b2", "route_id": "sprint_ista_northern_australia_exact_texts", "scope_classifier": "term_and_person_form_gate_v1", "section_id": "ntna13", "source_family": "structured_public_domain_books"}, "rejection_reason": "", "rights_access_status": "public_access_text_available", "secondary_role": "source_grounded_section_record", "source_label": "Medicine man", "source_name": "Internet Sacred Text Archive", "source_tier": "A", "source_type": "public_domain_transcribed_book", "title": "Medicine man in Magic and Medicine", "url": "https://sacred-texts.com/aus/ntna/ntna13.